cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of identifying same users across multiple devices based on browsing logs, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach utilizes a combination of unsupervised neural feature ensemble approach and supervised classification, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) and statistical learning (cs.SI). Lastly, the paper proposes supervised and unsupervised inference techniques, which can be related to the field of cryptography (cs.CR).
